    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\n`:h dev-name-common` states:\n\n> Do NOT use these deprecated nouns:\n    - buffer        Use \"buf\" instead\n    - command       Use \"cmd\" instead\n    - window        Use \"win\" instead\n\nBut `vim.keymap.set` receives `opts.buffer`\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. `nvim --clean -u NONE`\n2. `:lua vim.keymap.set('n', 'a', 'b', { buf = 3 })`\n3. Error\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n`buffer` is soft-deprecated (or never deprecated but just undocumented?) and replaced by `buf`. At least `buf` should work as option.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n3eab5bd38a5680066166a4e94c788ef345081dc7\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\n-\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nMacOS 14.7\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nGhostty 1.1.3\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ntmux-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
